[0.001, "o", "\u001b[1;32m[Info] 66 lines displayed\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[0m"]
[2.006, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.001, "o", "\u001b[1;34m/*\r\n\u001b[0m"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;34mThe output of the queries can be filtered line by line using these operators:\r\n\u001b[0m"]
[0.001, "o", "\u001b[1;34m\\==     strict different: line selected if none of the patterns matches the line.\r\n"]
[0.001, "o", "\u001b[0m"]
[0.001, "o", "\u001b[1;34m==      strict equal : line selected if at least one pattern matches the lines.\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[0m"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;34m<>      caseless different: same as \\== except caseless.\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[0m"]
[0.001, "o", "\u001b[1;34m=       caseless equal: same as == except caseless.\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[0m"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;34m*/\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[0m"]
[11.542, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.002, "o", "\u001b[1;34m"]
[0.000, "o", "/*\r\n\u001b[0m"]
[0.001, "o", "\u001b[1;34mIf the package regex.cls is available, then the operands starting with \"/\" are\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[0m"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;34m"]
[0.000, "o", "regular expressions which are compiled into a pattern. The matching with this\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[0m"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;34m"]
[0.000, "o", "pattern is then tested for each line.\r\n"]
